Japanese Ultra-Right Conservatives' Reckless Remarks under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- Never have so shameless and provocative outcries distorting and denying the history of aggression been heard from Japan as today. Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary assailing Foreign Minister Aso and other ultra-right conservatives for letting loose recently a string of jargons whitewashing the crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists in the past.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The voices blasting the unreasonable behavior of Japan are growing stronger in the world than ever before. Even the U.S. political circles and media are becoming critical of the Japanese right conservative politicians' frantic moves to whitewash the past crimes and revive militarism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's wrong attitude toward the history of aggression and its settlement proves that it does not want peace but aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's ultra-right conservatives are keen to instill a militarist viewpoint on history and the spirit of revenge deep into the Japanese people and create a social atmosphere to stage a comeback to Korea. This is evidenced by Japan's reality.
 Japan has already rounded off its material, military and legal arrangements for overseas aggression. What remains to be done is to put its scenario for overseas aggression into practice. Korea is made its primary target. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is tampering with its criminal history of brigandish occupation of Korea and colonial domination over it, while persistently evading its responsibility for settling its past. It is working hard to grab Tok Islet and concentrically deploying the main forces of the "Self-Defence Forces" in western Japan. All these moves clearly indicate that the Japanese militarists' moves for reinvasion of Korea have reached a reckless stage.
 No distortion can ever change history. It will remain unchanged despite the change of the era and the flow of the time.

Anti-reunification Remarks of Lawmaker from GNP under Fire in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- The Taejon and South Chungchong Provincial Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly released a statement on February 24, which slashed at the remarks made by Jon Ryo Ok, a lawmaker from the "Grand National Party," seriously damaging the meaning of the joint declaration.
 Accusing Jon of talking nonsense that the joint declaration "was bought," the statement termed this a childish judgment made by a person who failed to grasp the meaning of the declaration and a challenge to the people's desire for reunification in the June 15 era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such reckless behavior of the GNP as talking rubbish without elementary political sense can never be tolerated, it said, contending that any statesman should be responsible for his or her words and deeds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jon should own the responsibility for her remarks insulting the June 15 joint declaration that serves as guidelines for all the fellow countrymen desirous of national reunification and promptly quit the political camp, the statement urged.

RS. on Ideological and Moral Trait of Songun Revolutionary Fighters 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Monday says in a signed article that the general march of the Songun revolution today is an ideological onward movement to bring about a new turn not only in the economic field but in ideological consciousness and mental and moral trait of people as well.
 What is important in the ideological and moral trait of march fighters is the invariable revolutionary faith that they will firmly believe and follow leader Kim Jong Il only and share life and death with the headquarters of the revolution, the paper says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity of our army and people around Kim Jong Il is a basic guarantee for prosperity of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the noblest ideological and moral trait for the revolutionary soldiers to follow their leader invariably and share life and death with him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is also important in the ideological and moral trait of march fighters is confidence in certain victory of socialism and revolutionary optimism.
 Socialism and the destiny of Korean people are linked with each other as one. It is a lesson of history that the defence of socialism means victory but the abandonment of it means death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conviction that only socialism enables people to defend their dignity and right, true life and happiness, and optimism that Korean-style socialism will make a long drive,--this is the revolutionary faith of our army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The moves of the U.S. imperialists to isolate and stifle Korean-style socialism are now becoming more vicious, but they cannot break the revolutionary faith of our army and people who regard socialism as their life and soul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean army and people will continue to make leaping progress and innovation in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with the might of a revolutionary offensive, rallied close around Kim Jong Il.

Struggle against Anti-Reunification Forces Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- It is one of the major tasks before the three-point patriotic movement of the Korean people to struggle against the anti-reunification forces of south Korea including the "Grand National Party". Rodong Sinmun today says this in a by-lined article.
 It is the intrinsic requirements of the movement for national reunification to struggle against the anti-reunification forces, the article notes, and goes on:
 The Korean people have waged a stubborn struggle for smashing the challenges and obstructions of the anti-reunification forces at home and abroad in the whole course of the movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces in south Korea are a major obstacle to the patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity.
 The Koreans should regard the struggle against the anti-reunification forces as one of the major tasks before the three-point patriotic movement and wage an uncompromising struggle against the pro-U.S. conservative forces of south Korea opposed to national reconciliation and independent reunification. 
 The movement of Koreans for national reunification has developed into an all-people movement for reunification and patriotism irrespective of differences in ideology, political view and religious faith under the uplifted banner of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can match the united strength of the nation.
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces in south Korea zealously toeing the hostile policy of the U.S. imperialists towards the DPRK have become extremely frantic in their moves to perpetuate the national division and escalate the confrontation among compatriots. This reality urgently requires the Korean people to wage a more dynamic struggle for smashing their machinations. The steadily advancing movement for reunification alone can contribute to achieving the cause of national independence. In this sense reunification requires a struggle and vice versa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victory is always in store for the Korean people waging a dynamic struggle against the anti-reunification forces at home and abroad under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration.

Korean Painting Attracting World's Interest
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- KCNA recently interviewed with People's Artist Sonu Yong of the Mansudae Art Studio about the world's trend of fine art.
 Expressing what he had felt at the Eighth Beijing International Art Exhibition, Sonu said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition was attended by more than 300 fine art companies from over 20 countries including France and Singapore. Displayed there were over 10,000 pieces of art works. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The standings were decided by the method of bringing together the opinions of visitors at the exhibition where gold prizes were awarded to the Korean paintings "Lake Chon on Mt. Paektu" (by Sonu Yong) and "River Nam in Winter" (by Jong Chang Mo) respectively. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of art experts and fans appreciated the Korean pictures, saying that they boosted the realistic fine art onto a higher standard and represented the oriental pictures.
 He had felt this at international art exhibitions held in various countries and his individual ones, but it was at the recent Beijing exhibition that he was strongly impressed by the attention of the world fine art circles being focused on the realistic fine art, on the Korean paintings in particular, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for the secret of the Korean paintings attracting the attention of the world fine art circles, he went on to say: 
 People are charmed by the realistic fine art which reflects the beauty of humans and nature and is of cognitional and educational significance more than abstract pictures apart from realistic representation of the objective realities.
 The Korean painting with a long history reflects well the reality so as to give people cubic, chiaroscuro and infinitely spatial effects that one cannot feel at the European paintings based on surface representation and oriental paintings based on Indian ink and lines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean painting, which has turned from Indian ink painting to colored painting, is developing to suit the modern aesthetics, keeping the traditional drawing technique alive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, great master of art, the Juche-oriented fine art, which entered a new stage of development in the 1970s, is now at its heyday.
 The Korean painting will get more popular in the world fine art circles.
